Chinese-made vehicles are loaded on a cargo ship bound for Saudi Arabia at the Lianyungang Port in East China's Jiangsu Province on Monday. While domestic vehicle sales have been slowing, exports have seen steady growth. In 2018, China's total auto exports rose 11 percent to a record high of 1.15 million vehicles, according to official data. Photo: VCG
